main event: A bright white object that resembled a star was observed in Warrenton, Mo. on August 15, 1966.
interesting points: The object was in sight for 1 minute 15 seconds,The object moved erratically and disappeared suddenly to the north,The observer noted that the object was brighter than the brightest stars,It was during daylight conditions with slight cloud cover,The witness was outside and described the object as solid and light white.
sighted object: a bright white object resembling a star
witness description: A 47-year-old male who reported the sighting with another person named Carl Goff.
